# Root build context for the web image (built from repo root — pnpm workspace).
# WITHOUT this, `COPY web web` / `COPY packages/... ` would drag the host's
# node_modules (with host-specific pnpm symlinks) + build output into the image,
# clobbering the freshly pnpm-installed modules and breaking resolution (next build
# -> MODULE_NOT_FOUND). It also keeps the context small/fast. The codegen artifacts
# (packages/api-client/openapi.json + src/schema.d.ts) are intentionally NOT ignored.
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/.expo
**/.expo-shared
**/dist
**/build
**/.venv
**/__pycache__
**/*.tsbuildinfo
**/.pytest_cache
**/.ruff_cache
**/.mypy_cache
.git
.github
infra/terraform/.terraform
temp
